    "creation_date" : 1331557232,
    "answer_id" : 9667461,
    "question_id" : 2632419,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can use <code>Working sets</code>. From <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/a/2632809/2436175\">the same dropdown menu</a> on Open Resource dialog select <code>Select working set</code>. It opens up the working set dialogue where you can create working sets if you don't already have them.</p>\n\n<p>When creating a new one, choose the type <code>Resources</code> and select which folders in your workspace are consider as candidates for searching or for opening resources. I have included only <code>src</code> and <code>test</code> folders and usually <code>pom.xml</code>'s and other misc configuration files.</p>\n\n<p>With the couple of large projects I'm working on it has a noticeable impact on search speed too.</p>\n"
