    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1728889,
      "reputation" : 1889,
      "user_id" : 1582944,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/be313660cabc95feab5a0c2af56c27d7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Rajesh",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1582944/rajesh"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 153,
    "last_activity_date" : 1573149783,
    "last_edit_date" : 1573149783,
    "creation_date" : 1346344576,
    "answer_id" : 12201561,
    "question_id" : 2632419,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<ol>\n<li>Right click on the project and select <kbd>Properties</kbd>\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/yWneA.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/yWneA.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></li>\n<li>Expand <strong>Resource</strong> and click on <kbd>Resource Filters</kbd></li>\n<li>Click on <kbd>Add Filter...</kbd> to create a new filter\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/TKdGE.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/TKdGE.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></li>\n<li>On the dialog box that opens\n\n<ol>\n<li>Select the <kbd>Exclude all</kbd> and  <kbd>Files</kbd> radio buttons</li>\n<li>Under <strong>File and Folder Attributes</strong> enter <code>*.class</code></li>\n</ol></li>\n<li>Click <kbd>OK</kbd></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/J0QrR.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/J0QrR.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<p>To exclude an entire directory hierarchy, e.g. the <code>target</code> directory, select the <kbd>Files and folders</kbd> radio button and the <kbd>All children (recursive)</kbd> checkbox.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Edit</strong> </p>\n\n<p>Exclude the following for a complete cleanup of <code>Open Resource</code> dialog</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Files *.class</li>\n<li>Folder bin</li>\n<li>Folder build</li>\n<li>Folder target</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Without excluding all 4 it does not work.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3776879,
      "reputation" : 253,
      "user_id" : 3137478,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/6WaZ1.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Ilyas Soomro",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3137478/ilyas-soomro"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1400068314,
    "last_edit_date" : 1400068314,
    "creation_date" : 1400066969,
    "answer_id" : 23653428,
    "question_id" : 2632419,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Some time you are not able mark build or bin folder as Derived resource, because eclipse package explorer or project explorer does not show you build or bin folder in project view.</p>\n\n<p>What you need to do, to show build folder in project view:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Go to <code>Project &gt; Properties &gt; Java Build Path &gt; Source &gt;</code> change default output folder to build1\n<strong>Note: It will ask you to remove old folder and its content, Press No (to restore it later)</strong></p></li>\n<li><p>Now build folder is visible on package explorer, go to folder properties and mark it as Derived</p></li>\n<li>Now change your default output folder back to build (to restore old setting)</li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2918073,
      "reputation" : 1150,
      "user_id" : 2500882,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://graph.facebook.com/639972636/picture?type=large",
      "display_name" : "Nadav Finish",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2500882/nadav-finish"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1410161661,
    "last_edit_date" : 1410161661,
    "creation_date" : 1410160682,
    "answer_id" : 25719118,
    "question_id" : 2632419,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Eclipse Luna - just go to the following link\n<a href=\"http://help.eclipse.org/luna/index.jsp?topic=%2Forg.eclipse.platform.doc.user%2Ftasks%2Ftasks-48b.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://help.eclipse.org/luna/index.jsp?topic=%2Forg.eclipse.platform.doc.user%2Ftasks%2Ftasks-48b.htm</a>  <br>\n<strong>OR</strong> <br>\n1. Create a working set (include all projects)<br>\n2. On \"Package Explorer\" panel click on \"Filters\" (in the same menu you just created the working set) and deselect \"Inner class files\" + click ok</p>\n\n<p>That worked for me</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2137644,
      "reputation" : 17369,
      "user_id" : 1897010,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/mI4YJ.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Mujammil H Kazi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1897010/mujammil-h-kazi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1462186460,
    "creation_date" : 1462186460,
    "answer_id" : 36980727,
    "question_id" : 2632419,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Showing or hiding files in the Project Explorer view\nYou can choose to hide system files or generated class files in one of the navigation views. (System files are those that have only a file extension but no file name, for example .classpath.)</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>On the toolbar for the Project Explorer, click the Menu button Menu\n  button to open the drop-down menu of display options. Select Customize\n  View..,.</p>\n  \n  <p>In the dialog box that opens, select the Filters tab and then select\n  the checkboxes for the types of files that you want to hide. In\n  addition, you can restrict the displayed files to a working set.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/mQL2V.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/mQL2V.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a>\nOn the toolbar for the Project Explorer, click the Menu button Menu button to open the drop-down menu of display options.\nChoose Select Working Set...\nSelect an existing working set from the list or create a new one by selecting  NEw \n<a href=\"http://help.eclipse.org/luna/index.jsp?topic=%2Forg.eclipse.platform.doc.user%2Ftasks%2Ftasks-48b.htm\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">check here</a></p>\n"
  }, {
